Vancomycin Flushing Reaction (aka "Red man syndrome")
[edit]Vancomycin is recommended to be administered in a dilute solution slowly, over at least 60 min (maximum rate of 10 mg/min for doses >500 mg)[20] due to the high incidence of pain and thrombophlebitis and to avoid an infusion reaction known as vancomycin flushing reaction.

]
Intravenous
[edit]Vancomycin must be given intravenously for systemic therapy since it is poorly absorbed from the intestine.
